<plot>Columbia production number 3805: The camera, with Bill Stern's narration, records a day at West Point Military Academy with Dan Foldberg, Army's All-American end on the football team, a senior expected to graduate in the upcoming spring. Foldberg's day begins with reveille at 5:50 A.M. From that point on it's a grueling twelve hours of study, drill and football practice. The short concludes with action-scenes from the 1950 Army-Navy football game.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?111235</url></doc>
